<paragraph blockId="0.[136,1452,1798,1930]" pageId="0" pageNumber="163">
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. Valenz. &amp; E. Santiago" authorityYear="2022" box="[136,458,1798,1822]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Epidendrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chrisii-sharoniae">
<emphasis box="[136,458,1798,1822]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="163">Epidendrum chrisii-sharoniae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Hagsater (2004: 7" authorityName="Hagsater" authorityYear="2004" box="[600,1079,1798,1822]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Epidendrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="163" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cyclotylosum">
<emphasis box="[600,878,1798,1822]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="163">Epidendrum cyclotylosum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hagsater, E." box="[886,1079,1798,1822]" pageId="0" pageNumber="163" pagination="730" refId="ref2401" refString="Hagsater, E. (2004) Epidendrum cyclotylosum. In: Hagsater, E. &amp; Sanchez S., L. (Eds.) The Genus Epidendrum, Part 4. lcones Orchidacearum 7: pl. 730." type="journal article" year="2004">Hágsater (2004: 7</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(4), pl. 730) but has a strictly erect inflorescence with 7–18, non-resupinate, deep violet to atropurpureous flowers (vs. an arching inflorescence with 13–20 resupinate, pale brown-red flowers), a larger lip (7.0–8.0 × 7.0–9.0 vs. 3.0–4.0 x 
<quantity box="[981,1109,1870,1894]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" metricValueMax="4.7" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="0" pageNumber="163" unit="mm" value="4.1" valueMax="4.7" valueMin="3.5">3.5–4.7 mm</quantity>
) with the mid-lobe sub-quadrate (vs. semi-orbicular), and laminar, erect calli (vs. a single, sub-orbicular callus, slightly concave and striated at the base).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
